  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries worldwide. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key features typically include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n2. Customer identification and verification requirements\n3. Record-keeping standards\n4. Reporting of cash transactions above certain thresholds\n5. Sanctions for non-compliance\n\nOrganizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) help coordinate international AML standards and guidelines.",
